<br>
1. Several classes have popular weapons that have aggro producing procs - Earthcrafter has a 50% slow, Sword of the Lost Crusades has Stun Shock, Petrified Heartwood Flamberge has Root, etc. The list is actually pretty long. No one likes having to pull out a Windblade so the Warrior can get aggro.<br>
<br>
2. Knights have their equipment AND their spells. Frankly if you aren't a well-equipped Warrior what value do you have? Utility? ahaha!<br>
<br>
3. PoP stuff hits hard. If you can't grab initial aggro fast people are going to die and the group may get wiped out. It is not worth the risk when Knight can grab initial aggro fast unless you are very well equipped indeed.<br>
<br>
4. Warriors are mana sponges. Modestly equipped Wariors are a liability, not an asset. They are a huge mana burden.<br>
<br>
5. There is always an undercurrent of equipment=uber in the game. Several melee classes are able to get very nice weapons indeed from lesser mobs. Warriors need to kill the PoI dragon and AoW at a minimum to get weapons that can to the basic function needed by Warriors (aggro).<br>
<br>
When a Warrior is suggested as a member of a group, I'm certain any non-Warrior melees suggest that they can tank and getting a damage dealer would speed up experiance. The fact that sometimes melee classes other than Warriors MT at raids due to their ability to chain Stun for aggro, etc. bolsters their claim to be just as good at MTing, which is unfortunately our ONLY role.<br>
<br>
BB<br>
